1
00:00:39,633 --> 00:00:42,800
We successfully removed
the bullet from the lumbar area

2
00:00:42,933 --> 00:00:44,900
of the spine of your husband.

3
00:00:45,267 --> 00:00:45,967
That's great.

4
00:00:46,833 --> 00:00:48,567
<i> However, there are some things</i>

5
00:00:48,700 --> 00:00:50,567
<i>we still need to monitor
closely.</i>

6
00:00:51,467 --> 00:00:52,833
<i> What do you mean, Doc?</i>

7
00:00:54,600 --> 00:00:56,367
<i>- Is that your phone?
- Oh my...</i>

8
00:00:56,500 --> 00:00:58,967
<i> I think it's Ma'am Andrea's.</i>

9
00:00:59,100 --> 00:01:00,233
<i> Hello, Manuel?</i>

10
00:01:00,367 --> 00:01:03,333
<i> Hello, is this Miss Felma?</i>

11
00:01:03,467 --> 00:01:05,767
<i>I don't know why Andrea
called you.</i>

12
00:01:05,900 --> 00:01:08,900
<i>She said a lot
of hurtful stuff.</i>

13
00:01:09,067 --> 00:01:11,333
<i> We have a family emergency.</i>

14
00:01:11,800 --> 00:01:13,233
<i> Dad was shot.</i>

15
00:01:13,367 --> 00:01:14,933
<i> If you hadn't left...</i>

16
00:01:15,067 --> 00:01:16,567
<i>This wouldn't have
happened to you.</i>

17
00:01:16,700 --> 00:01:18,600
<i> 18 years, Manuel.</i>

18
00:01:18,733 --> 00:01:20,500
<i> I tried to love you.</i>

19
00:01:20,633 --> 00:01:24,400
<i>But you, I've never felt
your love even once.</i>

20
00:01:24,967 --> 00:01:26,733
<i>Now, you can't do
anything anymore.</i>

21
00:01:26,867 --> 00:01:29,433
<i> You'll still end up with me.</i>

22
00:01:29,567 --> 00:01:30,867
<i> Did you call Jessica?</i>

23
00:01:31,000 --> 00:01:33,033
<i>Andrea, I didn't raise you
to become rude.</i>

24
00:01:33,167 --> 00:01:34,533
<i> I didn't disrespect her, Mom.</i>

25
00:01:34,667 --> 00:01:37,833
<i>I'm only trying to defend
our family, especially you.</i>

26
00:01:37,967 --> 00:01:40,200
<i>Your dad is critical right now.</i>

27
00:01:40,867 --> 00:01:42,633
<i>Dad, you're awake!
Dad!</i>

28
00:01:43,900 --> 00:01:46,467
<i>Dad, you're finally awake!
Dad!</i>

29
00:01:47,500 --> 00:01:48,933
<i>Do you feel something from here?</i>

30
00:01:51,300 --> 00:01:52,333
<i> How about here?</i>

31
00:01:53,500 --> 00:01:56,033
<i>No. Can you try to curl
your toes?</i>

32
00:02:17,733 --> 00:02:19,133
- Be careful.
- Thank you.

33
00:02:19,267 --> 00:02:20,100
Careful.

34
00:02:21,167 --> 00:02:22,100
Dear, do you have
your packed lunch?

35
00:02:22,233 --> 00:02:22,967
I will, Dad.

36
00:02:23,100 --> 00:02:24,467
Listen to your teacher, okay?

37
00:02:24,600 --> 00:02:25,300
- I will.
- Don't be disobedient.

38
00:02:25,433 --> 00:02:26,700
You should be like me, okay?

39
00:02:26,833 --> 00:02:28,600
Bright, smart.

40
00:02:29,133 --> 00:02:30,500
- Yes, Dad.
- But that's okay?

41
00:02:30,633 --> 00:02:32,367
- Okay, good job!
- Yes of course, Dad.

42
00:02:32,500 --> 00:02:33,433
I became more energized

43
00:02:33,567 --> 00:02:34,567
because of the breakfast
Pretty Mama made.

44
00:02:34,700 --> 00:02:36,633
That's what I'm talking about.

45
00:02:36,767 --> 00:02:37,833
Be safe, sweetie.

46
00:02:38,433 --> 00:02:41,500
Please say our thanks
to Aunt Felma.

47
00:02:42,733 --> 00:02:44,800
- Let's go?
- I can manage, Mom.

48
00:02:44,933 --> 00:02:46,300
I can see the school from here.

49
00:02:46,567 --> 00:02:48,200
Let Dad bring you back home.

50
00:02:48,367 --> 00:02:49,867
I'll get going. Bye, Mom!

51
00:02:50,000 --> 00:02:51,567
- Bye, Dad!
- Bye, sweetie.

52
00:02:56,633 --> 00:02:58,267
Hey, no pressure, okay?

53
00:02:58,400 --> 00:03:01,100
You don't have to bring Tetay
to school every day.

54
00:03:01,767 --> 00:03:03,433
You can do that only
if it fits your schedule.

55
00:03:03,800 --> 00:03:05,633
I want to bring her to school
every day as long as I can.

56
00:03:06,767 --> 00:03:07,900
I can bring her to school
and even pick her up.

57
00:03:09,533 --> 00:03:11,667
So I can make up
for the lost years.

58
00:03:13,467 --> 00:03:16,933
I can even pursue you
at the same time if you like.

59
00:03:19,000 --> 00:03:20,667
Haven't we talked
about this already?

60
00:03:21,433 --> 00:03:23,633
Let's not rush everything.

61
00:03:24,033 --> 00:03:25,767
Let's take it slow. Okay?

62
00:03:28,167 --> 00:03:31,533
Maybe you're still in love
with Lance.

63
00:03:33,433 --> 00:03:35,600
Since he started hurting me...

64
00:03:36,867 --> 00:03:38,567
I saw who he really was...

65
00:03:39,133 --> 00:03:41,100
I slowly stopped loving him.

66
00:03:42,767 --> 00:03:45,567
I just put up with
being with him because...

67
00:03:45,700 --> 00:03:47,233
he threatened to hurt Tetay.

68
00:03:48,467 --> 00:03:51,000
Honestly, I've had enough.

69
00:03:51,133 --> 00:03:53,033
Hey, don't give up.

70
00:03:54,233 --> 00:03:55,733
I'm still going
to pursue you, remember?

71
00:03:57,167 --> 00:03:59,467
I'm only waiting for you
to get ready to love again.

72
00:04:03,267 --> 00:04:06,267
But, Jeff, I've changed a lot.

73
00:04:07,667 --> 00:04:10,567
Besides, are you sure
you still like me

74
00:04:10,700 --> 00:04:13,933
even though I was with Lance
for a long time?

75
00:04:15,133 --> 00:04:17,133
Why don't you just pursue
someone else?

76
00:04:19,133 --> 00:04:21,133
Your past with Lance
isn't an issue with me.

77
00:04:23,467 --> 00:04:25,467
Tetay was already there
before you became together.

78
00:04:27,567 --> 00:04:28,600
And who am I to judge?

79
00:04:28,733 --> 00:04:30,333
My family isn't perfect.

80
00:04:32,067 --> 00:04:32,933
We have a problem with our Dad,

81
00:04:33,067 --> 00:04:34,600
because he's still there.

82
00:04:35,133 --> 00:04:36,600
He still doesn't leave us alone.

83
00:04:36,933 --> 00:04:38,667
I only have one request
to ask, Daisy.

84
00:04:39,700 --> 00:04:41,333
Please don't close
your heart just yet.

85
00:04:44,500 --> 00:04:46,833
I hope when everything
gets fixed...

86
00:04:49,933 --> 00:04:51,567
you'll give me a chance
to be with you again.

87
00:04:53,433 --> 00:04:54,367
I'll wait.

88
00:05:04,967 --> 00:05:05,633
Doc...

89
00:05:06,600 --> 00:05:09,300
why I cannot move my legs?

90
00:05:10,433 --> 00:05:12,833
I can feel a little in my toe.

91
00:05:14,433 --> 00:05:15,533
What's the problem?

92
00:05:16,100 --> 00:05:19,733
Nurse Hazel, I'll order an MRI
to get a clearer picture

93
00:05:19,867 --> 00:05:23,600
of the injury and confirm
the extent of the damage.

94
00:05:25,600 --> 00:05:26,667
Damage?

95
00:05:27,133 --> 00:05:28,300
What damage?

96
00:05:29,033 --> 00:05:30,367
I'll explain it to him, Doc.

97
00:05:31,267 --> 00:05:32,200
If you need anything,

98
00:05:32,333 --> 00:05:33,700
don't hesitate to reach out.

99
00:05:34,333 --> 00:05:35,400
Nurse Hazel.

100
00:05:39,000 --> 00:05:39,700
Hazel.

101
00:05:41,100 --> 00:05:42,767
What damage is
the doctor talking about?

102
00:05:47,200 --> 00:05:48,000
Manuel...

103
00:05:48,433 --> 00:05:50,867
even though there isn't an
official diagnosis yet...

104
00:05:51,867 --> 00:05:56,600
I believe you have
a spinal cord injury.

105
00:05:58,433 --> 00:06:00,733
And based on
the physical test earlier...

106
00:06:03,500 --> 00:06:04,700
there's a possibility that...

107
00:06:07,567 --> 00:06:10,367
you could be paralyzed
from the waist down.

108
00:06:11,600 --> 00:06:16,033
That means
you can no longer walk.

109
00:06:19,567 --> 00:06:20,967
Hazel, you're wrong!

110
00:06:21,100 --> 00:06:23,267
- Mom, don't scare Dad.
- I'm not scaring him.

111
00:06:24,667 --> 00:06:26,900
I'm only telling you
what can happen,

112
00:06:27,033 --> 00:06:28,333
so we can be prepared.

113
00:06:28,867 --> 00:06:30,033
You're not a doctor!

114
00:06:30,633 --> 00:06:31,433
Much less God,

115
00:06:31,567 --> 00:06:33,900
to say whether
I can walk or not!

116
00:06:35,067 --> 00:06:37,267
Are you questioning
my being a nurse?

117
00:06:38,700 --> 00:06:40,833
I've worked in the hospital
for decades.

118
00:06:41,000 --> 00:06:43,000
I know what I'm talking about!

119
00:06:45,067 --> 00:06:47,067
I'm telling you
the truth because...

120
00:06:48,267 --> 00:06:49,900
I don't want you to hope
for nothing.

121
00:06:54,767 --> 00:06:57,467
You're only telling me that
because you hate me.

122
00:06:57,600 --> 00:06:59,300
You don't want me to leave you!

123
00:06:59,833 --> 00:07:01,500
I can't be disabled!

124
00:07:01,633 --> 00:07:02,600
I'll be able to walk!

125
00:07:02,733 --> 00:07:03,767
I can't...

126
00:07:05,733 --> 00:07:07,967
I can't end up paralyzed!

127
00:07:08,367 --> 00:07:09,133
No!

128
00:07:10,733 --> 00:07:13,033
I can't end up paralyzed!

129
00:07:15,733 --> 00:07:16,733
No!

130
00:07:17,233 --> 00:07:18,900
- Stop it, Manuel!
- I can't end up paralyzed!

131
00:07:19,033 --> 00:07:21,767
- That's enough!
- No!

132
00:07:22,933 --> 00:07:25,033
There's nothing you can do.

133
00:07:25,167 --> 00:07:28,500
Do you want your wound to bleed?

134
00:07:28,633 --> 00:07:29,967
Do you want your wound
to open up?

135
00:07:30,100 --> 00:07:31,600
Your condition will only get
worse.

136
00:07:31,733 --> 00:07:34,067
So stop!
There's nothing we can do.

137
00:07:35,167 --> 00:07:36,333
I can still walk again!

138
00:07:37,567 --> 00:07:38,833
I'll be able to walk!

139
00:07:41,200 --> 00:07:42,467
No.

140
00:07:42,600 --> 00:07:43,533
Dad.

141
00:07:43,667 --> 00:07:46,067
- We can get this Dad...
- No.

142
00:07:46,200 --> 00:07:48,433
I can't end up paralyzed!

143
00:07:56,400 --> 00:07:58,433
<i> We have a family emergency.</i>

144
00:07:58,567 --> 00:08:00,200
<i> Dad was shot.</i>

145
00:08:00,333 --> 00:08:02,133
<i>They've removed the bullet
from his spine</i>

146
00:08:02,267 --> 00:08:05,433
<i>but he's still in a critical
condition.</i>

147
00:08:13,600 --> 00:08:14,700
Sis?

148
00:08:16,833 --> 00:08:18,233
Hello, sis.

149
00:08:20,867 --> 00:08:22,633
Earth to sis!

150
00:08:27,900 --> 00:08:30,267
What were we talking
about again?

151
00:08:32,967 --> 00:08:34,433
We were talking about...

152
00:08:34,567 --> 00:08:36,633
the rescheduling of your
interview

153
00:08:36,767 --> 00:08:39,033
with Miss Abby of Pinoy Moms.

154
00:08:39,167 --> 00:08:40,133
That'll be tomorrow.

155
00:08:40,767 --> 00:08:41,433
Oh.

156
00:08:42,067 --> 00:08:43,200
That's good, right?

157
00:08:43,433 --> 00:08:44,833
The interview
will finally push through.

158
00:08:45,600 --> 00:08:47,033
And there's a new angle...

159
00:08:48,367 --> 00:08:49,700
our engagement.

160
00:08:50,700 --> 00:08:53,933
I think that's more than enough
to cover up your viral issue.

161
00:08:55,367 --> 00:08:57,600
Let's push it, sis!
Push!

162
00:08:59,367 --> 00:09:01,200
Do we really need to do that?

163
00:09:01,333 --> 00:09:02,200
Felma...

164
00:09:03,667 --> 00:09:04,733
are you okay?

165
00:09:05,233 --> 00:09:06,500
Is there something
bothering you?

166
00:09:08,100 --> 00:09:08,967
Oh...

167
00:09:12,400 --> 00:09:15,667
Looks like you need privacy.

168
00:09:15,800 --> 00:09:18,500
Oops, sorry.
Excuse me.

169
00:09:23,600 --> 00:09:24,700
Oh...

170
00:09:26,233 --> 00:09:27,467
Noah, it's because of...

171
00:09:28,533 --> 00:09:29,633
Is it because...

172
00:09:30,233 --> 00:09:32,067
you're bothered
about the viral video?

173
00:09:32,933 --> 00:09:34,433
Is that what's troubling you?

174
00:09:35,833 --> 00:09:39,167
That's why it might be better
to counter this viral video

175
00:09:39,933 --> 00:09:40,867
with this interview.

176
00:09:42,733 --> 00:09:46,633
So we can clear
your issue head on.

177
00:09:47,900 --> 00:09:48,633
Do you agree?

178
00:09:53,967 --> 00:09:54,933
I agree.

179
00:09:57,267 --> 00:09:58,733
Let's push through
with the interview.

180
00:10:06,933 --> 00:10:07,800
Mom...

181
00:10:08,300 --> 00:10:10,433
what if Dad
can no longer walk?

182
00:10:12,800 --> 00:10:14,167
Then he has to use a wheelchair.

183
00:10:15,267 --> 00:10:18,567
Unless there's a miracle,
and your dad would be healed.

184
00:10:19,433 --> 00:10:20,567
But I don't want
to get my hopes up.

185
00:10:21,467 --> 00:10:22,800
A paralyzed person...

186
00:10:23,433 --> 00:10:25,000
can never walk again.

187
00:10:25,633 --> 00:10:27,900
If that happens,
I'll take care of Dad.

188
00:10:29,567 --> 00:10:30,333
Really?

189
00:10:31,200 --> 00:10:32,400
Just a heads up...

190
00:10:33,500 --> 00:10:36,233
it's so difficult to care
for a paralyzed person.

191
00:10:36,933 --> 00:10:39,600
It takes physical strength
and a lot of patience.

192
00:10:39,733 --> 00:10:41,967
Just thinking about it
already tires me out

193
00:10:42,267 --> 00:10:45,067
But, Mom, you're totally
equipped to take care of Dad.

194
00:10:46,200 --> 00:10:48,433
Believe me,
it's harder and more draining

195
00:10:48,567 --> 00:10:50,200
to take care of a family member.

196
00:10:50,333 --> 00:10:51,867
It'd be better if your patient
isn't someone close to you,

197
00:10:52,433 --> 00:10:53,433
if your patient
were someone else.

198
00:10:53,567 --> 00:10:54,667
At least then your motivation,

199
00:10:54,800 --> 00:10:56,167
would be getting paid afterward.

200
00:10:56,300 --> 00:10:58,733
Of course, that doesn't apply
when you took care of family.

201
00:11:00,100 --> 00:11:02,700
Well, at least you get to take
care of someone you love.

202
00:11:03,167 --> 00:11:04,800
This is your dad's fault.

203
00:11:05,800 --> 00:11:07,500
He acted like a hero
to those two old folks,

204
00:11:07,667 --> 00:11:08,833
he wasn't even related
to them in any way.

205
00:11:09,633 --> 00:11:11,100
If he hadn't left us,

206
00:11:11,233 --> 00:11:13,100
this wouldn't have happened
to him.

207
00:11:13,533 --> 00:11:15,900
But, Mom, he left because you
fought with him.

208
00:11:16,767 --> 00:11:18,667
I fought with him because
of Felma

209
00:11:18,800 --> 00:11:20,133
and his illegitimate family.

210
00:11:20,267 --> 00:11:22,467
If you think about it,
it was Felma's fault.

211
00:11:22,867 --> 00:11:23,700
And now...

212
00:11:24,267 --> 00:11:25,333
where's Felma?

213
00:11:25,467 --> 00:11:26,367
Who will take care of him?

214
00:11:26,500 --> 00:11:28,400
Isn't it me?
Isn't it us?

215
00:11:28,933 --> 00:11:31,800
And most of all,
he'll still depend on my money!

216
00:11:32,500 --> 00:11:34,367
Mom, please don't talk
like that.

217
00:11:34,500 --> 00:11:36,867
Dad might wake up and hear you.

218
00:11:53,067 --> 00:11:54,100
Sis...

219
00:11:54,233 --> 00:11:57,333
Noah and the kids are already in
the reception area.

220
00:11:57,467 --> 00:11:59,633
That's where they set up
the interview.

221
00:11:59,767 --> 00:12:01,300
Are you ready?

222
00:12:02,267 --> 00:12:03,167
What?

223
00:12:03,700 --> 00:12:05,167
Okay.

224
00:12:05,433 --> 00:12:06,167
Thank you.

225
00:12:06,300 --> 00:12:07,867
Will you be there
in five minutes?

226
00:12:09,033 --> 00:12:10,233
Promise.

227
00:12:31,933 --> 00:12:34,167
So, prepare yourself, Jessica...

228
00:12:34,633 --> 00:12:36,267
to take care of your dad.

229
00:12:37,833 --> 00:12:40,900
From school,
you should go straight home.

230
00:12:41,233 --> 00:12:43,133
Because you're definitely in
for something tough.

231
00:12:55,033 --> 00:12:56,500
<i>Why do you have contact
with Andrea?</i>

232
00:12:56,633 --> 00:12:58,800
<i> She called me and she...</i>

233
00:12:58,933 --> 00:13:00,833
<i> she was so angry.</i>

234
00:13:01,333 --> 00:13:03,867
<i>She thought she was talking
to Dad.</i>

235
00:13:04,000 --> 00:13:06,400
<i>I don't know why Andrea
called you.</i>

236
00:13:06,533 --> 00:13:09,233
<i>She said a lot
of hurtful stuff.</i>

237
00:13:09,700 --> 00:13:12,300
<i>But, please, tell her not
to drag Dad</i>

238
00:13:12,433 --> 00:13:14,133
<i> into her anger at my mom.</i>

239
00:13:14,267 --> 00:13:16,500
<i> And please, not now.</i>

240
00:13:16,633 --> 00:13:18,700
<i> We're in the middle of crisis.</i>

241
00:13:18,833 --> 00:13:20,800
<i> Dad was shot.</i>

242
00:13:20,933 --> 00:13:22,333
<i> What you did was wrong.</i>

243
00:13:22,500 --> 00:13:24,833
<i> You involved someone innocent.</i>

244
00:13:24,967 --> 00:13:27,367
<i>I didn't know that
she was going through</i>

245
00:13:27,500 --> 00:13:28,900
<i> his father's phone.</i>

246
00:13:29,033 --> 00:13:30,900
<i>And why does it seem that
you're mad at me?</i>

247
00:13:31,033 --> 00:13:34,167
<i>I'm only defending you
against Hazel.</i>

248
00:13:34,300 --> 00:13:36,400
<i>She shouldn't have spread
your video.</i>

249
00:13:36,533 --> 00:13:38,933
<i>Mom, I'm just defending
our family...</i>

250
00:13:39,067 --> 00:13:40,133
<i> especially you.</i>

251
00:13:56,833 --> 00:13:57,800
Who is that?

252
00:14:14,800 --> 00:14:15,533
Why don't you answer it?

253
00:14:15,667 --> 00:14:16,600
Who's calling?

254
00:14:17,367 --> 00:14:18,300
It's Ava, Mom.

255
00:14:18,600 --> 00:14:20,567
I asked her to update me
on the schoolwork

256
00:14:20,700 --> 00:14:22,600
since I've been absent lately.

257
00:14:22,900 --> 00:14:23,867
I'll just take it.

258
00:14:33,267 --> 00:14:34,433
Hello, Ms. Felma?

259
00:14:37,333 --> 00:14:38,400
<i> Hi, Jessica...</i>

260
00:14:39,733 --> 00:14:42,467
<i>Thank you for answering my call.</i>

261
00:14:42,900 --> 00:14:44,367
Why did you call?

262
00:14:44,933 --> 00:14:47,933
I'm sorry about Andrea.

263
00:14:49,833 --> 00:14:50,767
She didn't...

264
00:14:51,733 --> 00:14:54,933
know that her words were hurtful
to you.

265
00:14:56,400 --> 00:14:57,700
<i> She couldn't...</i>

266
00:14:58,533 --> 00:15:03,800
control her feelings
because of the viral video.

267
00:15:03,967 --> 00:15:08,067
She feels that
your mom did that.

268
00:15:08,633 --> 00:15:09,867
Like I said last time,

269
00:15:10,000 --> 00:15:11,833
I get where she's coming from.

270
00:15:12,500 --> 00:15:14,100
<i> I'm glad to hear that.</i>

271
00:15:14,767 --> 00:15:18,267
I also appreciate that you
called.

272
00:15:18,833 --> 00:15:21,633
Because of that,
I was able to learn

273
00:15:21,767 --> 00:15:23,233
about your dad's condition.

274
00:15:24,867 --> 00:15:29,133
Believe it or not,
I'm praying for you.

275
00:15:30,433 --> 00:15:31,800
Your whole family.

276
00:15:32,833 --> 00:15:33,967
Thank you, Ms. Felma.

277
00:15:34,100 --> 00:15:35,767
It really means a lot.

278
00:15:36,333 --> 00:15:38,067
How's your dad?

279
00:15:38,867 --> 00:15:41,033
He already woke up
after the surgery.

280
00:15:41,167 --> 00:15:44,667
<i> They're just monitoring
how severe</i> the effects will be.

281
00:15:48,667 --> 00:15:51,333
But Mom said
there's a big chance that...

282
00:15:51,467 --> 00:15:52,200
Jessica!

283
00:15:57,567 --> 00:15:58,633
Who are you talking to?

284
00:16:02,067 --> 00:16:03,867
I said who are you talking to?

285
00:16:04,367 --> 00:16:05,633
Who is it?

286
00:16:05,767 --> 00:16:07,100
- I said who are you talking to?
- Mom, give it back to me!

287
00:16:07,233 --> 00:16:08,733
- No, mom! Mom! Mom!
- Give me that!

288
00:16:09,033 --> 00:16:09,967
<i>- Mom!
- Give it to me!</i>

289
00:16:10,100 --> 00:16:11,167
Give it to me!

290
00:16:16,467 --> 00:16:17,933
Why are you talking
to this woman?

291
00:16:19,000 --> 00:16:19,567
What?

292
00:16:21,367 --> 00:16:23,467
Hey! Felma the mistress!

293
00:16:24,167 --> 00:16:25,533
You're such a trouble,
you really are!

294
00:16:26,733 --> 00:16:27,933
Leave us alone!

295
00:16:28,067 --> 00:16:30,767
- The nerve of you to call!
- Mom, please stop.

296
00:16:30,900 --> 00:16:32,900
What do you need
from my daughter?

297
00:16:33,033 --> 00:16:34,600
What's your plan?

298
00:16:34,733 --> 00:16:36,833
Are you going to poison her mind
to turn her against me?

299
00:16:37,433 --> 00:16:39,733
Or are you going to use her to
take Manuel away from me?

300
00:16:39,867 --> 00:16:40,467
What?

301
00:16:41,100 --> 00:16:43,000
You, desperate woman!

302
00:16:43,767 --> 00:16:46,633
If I caught you calling my
daughter or my husband again,

303
00:16:46,767 --> 00:16:49,167
I will go to the Philippines
to attack you!

304
00:16:49,300 --> 00:16:52,867
I'll shove all the sausages
you make down your throat!

305
00:16:53,000 --> 00:16:54,333
- Mom, please stop!
- You shameless!

306
00:16:54,467 --> 00:16:55,600
I hope you die!

307
00:17:42,900 --> 00:17:44,467
Do you think I won't catch you?

308
00:17:45,567 --> 00:17:46,900
You even lied to me.

309
00:17:48,100 --> 00:17:50,967
You told me you were talking
to your friend.

310
00:17:51,500 --> 00:17:52,333
Huh?

311
00:17:53,300 --> 00:17:54,133
Why?

312
00:17:54,733 --> 00:17:55,800
I knew it.

313
00:17:56,667 --> 00:17:58,333
I had a feeling you're doing
something foolish

314
00:17:58,467 --> 00:17:59,567
with your dad's phone.

315
00:17:59,700 --> 00:18:00,833
And I was right!

316
00:18:01,867 --> 00:18:02,967
Now, tell me.

317
00:18:03,433 --> 00:18:04,900
When did you start betraying me?

318
00:18:05,400 --> 00:18:07,233
Since when are you talking
to Felma?

319
00:18:08,167 --> 00:18:09,800
Tell me!

320
00:18:12,300 --> 00:18:14,767
Mom, it was just an accident.

321
00:18:14,900 --> 00:18:18,700
I took Andrea's call
for Dad.

322
00:18:19,100 --> 00:18:21,600
She said a lot of hurtful stuff.

323
00:18:22,233 --> 00:18:25,533
But when I tried to call her
to avenge...

324
00:18:26,533 --> 00:18:29,467
that's when I accidentally
talked to Miss Felma.

325
00:18:30,800 --> 00:18:34,300
Miss Felma? Andrea?

326
00:18:34,433 --> 00:18:35,567
Why? Is she your sister?

327
00:18:36,433 --> 00:18:38,000
Since when?

328
00:18:38,900 --> 00:18:41,133
What does that woman want?

329
00:18:41,500 --> 00:18:42,933
Why is she calling you?

330
00:18:46,433 --> 00:18:50,533
Mom, she only wanted to
apologize for Andrea's behavior.

331
00:18:50,833 --> 00:18:52,833
And she only wants to know how
everything is going on, Mom.

332
00:18:52,967 --> 00:18:54,833
You even give them updates on
what's going here?

333
00:18:55,233 --> 00:18:58,667
You shouldn't have told them
what happened to your dad!

334
00:18:58,800 --> 00:19:00,200
But, Mom, they also have
the right to know

335
00:19:00,333 --> 00:19:02,300
because they are Dad's
original family.

336
00:19:02,433 --> 00:19:04,033
Knock it off!
Do you understand?

337
00:19:04,167 --> 00:19:05,233
Stop!

338
00:19:05,867 --> 00:19:08,167
You only found out
about them recently.

339
00:19:08,967 --> 00:19:11,367
We are the legal family.

340
00:19:11,500 --> 00:19:12,600
Do you understand?

341
00:19:13,767 --> 00:19:14,933
We're the only ones
who have the right.

342
00:19:15,067 --> 00:19:17,900
It's only us who have the right
to your Dad!

343
00:19:19,667 --> 00:19:22,067
Don't you ever tell your Dad
that you're talking to them.

344
00:19:22,200 --> 00:19:23,333
Do you understand?

345
00:19:27,067 --> 00:19:28,467
Do you understand?

346
00:19:39,900 --> 00:19:42,200
<i>Felma the mistress!
Felma the mistress!</i>

347
00:19:42,333 --> 00:19:44,133
<i>Felma the mistress!
Felma the mistress!</i>

348
00:19:44,267 --> 00:19:46,267
<i>Felma the mistress!
Felma the mistress!</i>

349
00:19:48,133 --> 00:19:49,700
<i> Honestly,</i>

350
00:19:49,833 --> 00:19:52,233
<i>I now have a peaceful
and happy life...</i>

351
00:19:55,233 --> 00:19:56,767
<i> with my kids.</i>

352
00:19:58,400 --> 00:20:02,567
<i>So I hope Manuel, Hazel,
and Jessica,</i>

353
00:20:04,400 --> 00:20:06,467
<i>have peaceful
and happy lives, too.</i>

354
00:20:07,333 --> 00:20:11,667
<i>Please remove all
the hatred in my heart.</i>

355
00:20:13,100 --> 00:20:14,733
In our hearts.

356
00:20:15,633 --> 00:20:20,300
<i>Slowly, until we can
forgive them.</i>

357
00:20:24,533 --> 00:20:26,000
Mom, we're ready to roll.

358
00:20:28,800 --> 00:20:29,600
Mom.

359
00:20:34,333 --> 00:20:36,133
What's the problem, Mom?

360
00:20:38,467 --> 00:20:40,233
Are you nervous?

361
00:20:40,700 --> 00:20:42,067
Here's some tissue, Mom.

362
00:20:43,433 --> 00:20:44,500
Thank you, Dear.

363
00:20:50,333 --> 00:20:52,000
I can't be nervous.

364
00:20:53,433 --> 00:20:56,933
Because my goal after the
interview,

365
00:20:57,500 --> 00:21:00,167
everyone should stop bashing
or bullying me.

366
00:21:00,400 --> 00:21:01,567
Even you, guys.

367
00:21:02,033 --> 00:21:04,200
I hope they forget...

368
00:21:05,133 --> 00:21:07,267
about the viral video.

369
00:21:08,933 --> 00:21:09,967
Okay, Mom!

370
00:21:10,567 --> 00:21:11,900
That's the attitude!

371
00:21:12,267 --> 00:21:13,933
Let's go for gold.

372
00:21:15,367 --> 00:21:17,333
Come here, give me a hug, Dear.

373
00:21:24,567 --> 00:21:25,867
I'm sorry.

374
00:21:26,133 --> 00:21:28,067
All of you, especially you,

375
00:21:28,200 --> 00:21:31,067
were affected by my video.

376
00:21:32,100 --> 00:21:35,567
Mom, I'm not blaming you.

377
00:21:37,200 --> 00:21:39,500
You even missed school.

378
00:21:40,667 --> 00:21:42,200
I'm sorry about that.

379
00:21:43,433 --> 00:21:44,333
Mom...

380
00:21:45,533 --> 00:21:49,967
I got annoyed with my classmates
who bash, and bully me.

381
00:21:50,833 --> 00:21:53,933
But you know what, Mom?
I am never ashamed of you.

382
00:21:54,767 --> 00:21:55,800
As in never.

383
00:21:57,667 --> 00:21:59,033
Thank you, Dear.

384
00:22:04,200 --> 00:22:06,900
And I promise, Mom.

385
00:22:07,300 --> 00:22:10,833
I'll be braver in handling
bullies and bashers.

386
00:22:12,167 --> 00:22:13,533
Because I realized,

387
00:22:13,667 --> 00:22:16,467
that it was wrong
to miss my school...

388
00:22:16,733 --> 00:22:20,467
or cut my classes just
to avoid my rude classmates.

389
00:22:20,600 --> 00:22:22,700
That's what I like about you,
Dear.

390
00:22:22,833 --> 00:22:26,867
Yes, Mom, I'll become a loser
if I do that.

391
00:22:27,100 --> 00:22:30,600
They've already destroyed my
self-confidence.

392
00:22:31,167 --> 00:22:35,633
Should I also sacrifice my
studies just to avoid them?

393
00:22:35,967 --> 00:22:38,467
No way!

394
00:22:39,000 --> 00:22:40,867
- Right, Mom? And...
- Of course.

395
00:22:41,000 --> 00:22:43,400
You didn't raise us to become
losers.

396
00:22:44,533 --> 00:22:46,467
I love you, Dear.

397
00:22:46,600 --> 00:22:47,933
I love you too, Mom.

398
00:22:48,100 --> 00:22:52,500
You're our perfect role model to
become successful in life.

399
00:22:52,633 --> 00:22:53,333
Oh...

400
00:22:53,900 --> 00:22:55,767
Thank you, Dear.
I love you.

401
00:22:58,167 --> 00:22:59,700
I love you, Mom.

402
00:23:03,333 --> 00:23:06,433
The MRI results showed
a significant damage,

403
00:23:06,567 --> 00:23:08,000
to the spinal cord.

404
00:23:08,567 --> 00:23:11,767
This means paralysis
from waist down.

405
00:23:12,233 --> 00:23:13,333
I knew it.

406
00:23:14,833 --> 00:23:15,767
See?

407
00:23:17,000 --> 00:23:18,033
I told you, right?

408
00:23:20,033 --> 00:23:22,533
I understand this
is a difficult news,

409
00:23:22,700 --> 00:23:25,400
but we will work with you
in every step of the way

410
00:23:25,533 --> 00:23:27,167
to help you adjust
with your condition.

411
00:23:27,300 --> 00:23:28,233
What do you mean by adjust?

412
00:23:28,367 --> 00:23:30,067
Is there no chance of me
walking again?

413
00:23:30,200 --> 00:23:31,867
I'll be forever like this?

414
00:23:33,033 --> 00:23:34,967
Is there no solution, Doc?
No cure?

415
00:23:35,300 --> 00:23:37,967
Manuel, stop yelling
at the doctor.

416
00:23:38,833 --> 00:23:41,400
There's nothing we can do with
your situation but accept it.

417
00:23:41,533 --> 00:23:43,233
Even if you get mad
at all the doctors...

418
00:23:43,367 --> 00:23:44,800
or all of us,

419
00:23:45,067 --> 00:23:46,833
that won't change your
condition.

420
00:23:49,333 --> 00:23:50,200
Please excuse us.

421
00:23:50,333 --> 00:23:52,200
We'll give you more time
to process the news.

422
00:23:52,333 --> 00:23:53,467
Thank you, Doc.

423
00:23:54,300 --> 00:23:55,667
No, come back here!

424
00:23:56,367 --> 00:23:58,033
Come back here! Cure me!

425
00:23:58,167 --> 00:24:00,300
Hey! Hey!
Come back here!

426
00:24:00,433 --> 00:24:01,567
Heal me!

427
00:24:02,400 --> 00:24:04,300
Prove that you're a good doctor!

428
00:24:04,433 --> 00:24:06,333
And you can make me walk again!

429
00:24:06,900 --> 00:24:08,000
Come back!

430
00:24:08,400 --> 00:24:10,600
Dad, we'll get through this,
okay?

431
00:24:10,733 --> 00:24:12,267
We'll take care of you.

432
00:24:12,400 --> 00:24:13,900
- No.
- We're here for you, Dad.

433
00:24:14,033 --> 00:24:15,500
- Dad, okay?
- No, Dear.

434
00:24:15,633 --> 00:24:17,067
They're fooling us!

435
00:24:17,200 --> 00:24:20,167
No! They're messing with us!

436
00:24:20,300 --> 00:24:22,033
I can still walk again, Dear!

437
00:24:22,333 --> 00:24:23,800
- That's enough, Dad.
- Hey!

438
00:24:23,933 --> 00:24:25,900
- Manuel!
- Come back here!

439
00:24:26,033 --> 00:24:27,067
Manuel, stop!

440
00:24:27,200 --> 00:24:29,033
Heal me!

441
00:24:30,000 --> 00:24:33,433
I'll be able to walk again.
I can't be paralyzed.

442
00:24:34,500 --> 00:24:38,400
- I can't be paralyzed.
- That's enough, Dad.

443
00:24:38,533 --> 00:24:40,433
Enough. Please stop.

444
00:24:44,900 --> 00:24:47,067
Dad.

445
00:24:47,200 --> 00:24:50,833
<i>Miss Felma, I have sad
and bad news.</i>

446
00:24:50,967 --> 00:24:53,600
<i>Dad is paralyzed
from the waist down.</i>

447
00:24:56,800 --> 00:24:58,467
- Mom! Mom!
- Felma!

448
00:24:58,700 --> 00:25:00,933
I don't want to lose you, Dad.

449
00:25:01,067 --> 00:25:04,100
- I wish I had died.
- Dad!

450
00:25:04,267 --> 00:25:06,033
Why did they save me?

451
00:25:08,300 --> 00:25:10,367
That's the reason
why you collapsed earlier.

452
00:25:10,733 --> 00:25:11,600
I'm sorry.

453
00:25:11,733 --> 00:25:14,833
Are you planning to tell your
original family

454
00:25:14,967 --> 00:25:16,467
about your situation?

455
00:25:16,800 --> 00:25:18,467
They don't care
about me anymore.

456
00:25:18,733 --> 00:25:19,700
That's not true.

457
00:25:20,000 --> 00:25:21,833
Miss Felma cares about you.

458
00:25:21,967 --> 00:25:23,700
Should we call Miss Felma?

459
00:25:23,967 --> 00:25:25,467
Won't you worry about him?

460
00:25:25,600 --> 00:25:29,033
For you and
for our relationship, no.

461
00:25:29,867 --> 00:25:34,100
I will stop calling and
receiving calls from them.
